entries.title: Meta says it will restore Trump's Facebook and Instagram accounts after two-year ban
See tense exchange between Santos and CNN reporter
entries.description: The campaign of embattled Rep. George Santos (R-NY) filed updated reports with federal regulators that appear to raise fresh questions about the source of the substantial personal loans he said he made to his campaign. CNN's Jessica Dean has the details.

entries.title: The announcement comes just hours after Germany said it will send Leopard 2 tanks. Russia says the decision brings the war 'to a new level'
Biden announces US will send Abrams tanks to Ukraine, hours after German decision to send Leopard 2 tanks
Late night hosts mock James Cameron, Tom Cruise after Oscar nominees revealed
entries.description: Wanda Sykes, James Corden, Jimmy Fallon and other late night hosts poked fun at the 95th annual Academy Awards nominations which were announced on Tuesday.

entries.title: Retired general on what will happen after Ukraine gets tanks
entries.description: The United States and Germany announced they are sending Abrams and Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine. CNN's John King speaks with Retired Lt. Gen. Mark Hertling on when the tanks will be ready for use.

entries.title: Thomas Bangalter of Daft Punk announces solo album and reveals his face
entries.description: Daft Punk's Thomas Bangalter announced he is releasing a solo album and is showing his face in public for the first time.

entries.title: Classic 'GoldenEye 007' game is coming to Nintendo Switch and Xbox
entries.description: James Bond fans may be waiting on the next actor who will play the British spy onscreen, but a beloved Bond adventure of yore is making its return.

entries.title: IOC clears path for Russian and Belarusian athletes to participate in upcoming Olympic Games
entries.description: The International Olympic Committee (IOC) outlined a multi-step plan for Russian and Belarusian athletes to participate at the upcoming 2024 Summer Games in Paris and the 2026 Winter Games in Milan.

entries.title: Consumer Reports calls Ford's automated driving tech much better than Tesla's
entries.description: Tesla's Autopilot, which at its core combines lane keeping assist with traffic aware cruise control to help guide a car down a highway, was once groundbreaking technology.

entries.title: This may be the only way to stop social media from harming our kids
entries.description: Tech executives could face the prospect of time behind bars in Britain if they willfully ignore rules designed to protect children online under a proposed amendment to an online safety bill.

entries.title: 'Tragedy upon tragedy': 44 hours. 3 mass shootings. 19 dead
Barcelona Femení become first team to win 50 consecutive league games
entries.description: Barcelona Femení have made history by becoming the first football team to win 50 consecutive league games.

entries.title: How Microsoft could use ChatGPT to supercharge its products
entries.description: Is ChatGPT the new Clippy?

entries.title: How M&M's is making the most of its spokescandies controversy
entries.description: Over the past year, M&M's has been the subject of Fox News tirades and criticism from a small segment of fans — first for changing the Green M&M's footwear and more recently featuring female M&M characters on its packaging for International Women's Day.

entries.title: Four Australian Open spectators 'revealed inappropriate flags and symbols and threatened security guards,' organizer says
entries.description: Four people attending the Australian Open were questioned by Victoria Police after they "revealed inappropriate flags and symbols and threatened security guards," a Tennis Australia spokesperson told CNN on Wednesday.

entries.title: Three sites 'in danger' added to UNESCO World Heritage List
entries.description: The historic center of the Ukrainian port city of Odesa and sites in Yemen and Lebanon were added to the World Heritage List Wednesday by the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO).

entries.title: The real problem with 'mummies'
entries.description: Mummies tend to spark feelings of the uncanny because they hover on an uncomfortable line between living and dead, between human and object.

entries.title: Meet the real-life zombie fungi that inspired 'The Last of Us'
entries.description: The zombies are identifiable by the fungi bursting from their bodies: a thicket of spiky tendrils, a miniature garden of mushroom-like fruiting bodies. These fungal parasites act as puppeteers, commanding and positioning the zombies to infect entire communities.

entries.title: Only two bodies from the Battle of Waterloo had ever been found -- until one man revealed what was in his attic
entries.description: Bones thought to belong to soldiers killed at the Battle of Waterloo have been discovered in an attic in Belgium.

entries.title: Biden: 'There is no offensive threat to Russia if Russian troops return to Russia'
entries.description: Germany confirmed it will send a long-demanded contingent of Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine in a major sign of support for Kyiv that will be matched by the United States.

entries.title: Analysis: Why sending tanks represents fierce new step by West
entries.description: Even in disarray, the message ends up being one of unity.

entries.title: Earth's inner core may have stopped turning and could go into reverse, study suggests
entries.description: The rotation of Earth's inner core may have paused and it could even go into reverse, new research suggests.

entries.title: Iran's amassed enough material for 'several nuclear weapons,' says IAEA chief
entries.description: Diplomatic efforts to prevent Iran developing a nuclear weapon should restart, said International Atomic Energy Agency chief Rafael Grossi, who warned that Tehran has amassed enough material for "several nuclear weapons."

entries.title: Iceberg roughly the size of London breaks off in Antarctica
entries.description: An iceberg nearly the size of Greater London broke off the Brunt Ice Shelf in Antarctica on Sunday according to the British Antarctic Survey.

entries.title: Revamped $2 million tournament signals new era for chess
entries.description: With its popularity soaring and games increasingly moving to online platforms, chess appears to be ushering in a new era.

entries.title: Photo of Delta flight attendant goes viral. See why
entries.description: Floyd Dean-Shannon, a Delta flight attendant, joins "CNN This Morning" to discuss a viral photo of him comforting a nervous passenger mid-flight.

entries.title: Julian Sands: Brother fears he's gone forever as authorities have 'no evidence' of his location
entries.description: Nick Sands, the brother of Julian Sands, has told a UK publication he knows "in my heart that he has gone" as California authorities continue to search for the actor.

entries.title: Microsoft cloud outage hits users around the world
entries.description: Microsoft on Wednesday said it had recovered all of its cloud services after a networking outage took down its cloud platform Azure along with services such as Teams and Outlook used by millions around the globe.

entries.title: As Israel bans Palestinian flags, one artist protests with his brush
entries.description: Just over a decade ago, the Palestinian flag hung alongside Israeli and American flags at the Israeli prime minister's residence, when Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas shared a historic handshake.

entries.title: Asia's richest man slams short-seller's fraud claims as 'baseless' and 'malicious'
entries.description: India's Adani Group on Wednesday denounced allegations of fraud made by US-based short seller Hindenburg Research as "baseless" and a "malicious combination of selective misinformation."

entries.title: Jeremy Renner was crushed by snowcat as he tried to save nephew, sheriff's report says
entries.description: Actor Jeremy Renner was attempting to stop his sliding snowcat from hitting his nephew when he was pulled under the snow-clearing vehicle and crushed on New Year's Day, according to a Washoe County Sheriff's Office incident report.

entries.title: Kremlin responds after Germans announce tanks for Ukraine
entries.description: Germany has confirmed that it will send Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine following weeks of diplomatic pressure. Chancellor Olaf Scholz announced the move in a cabinet meeting, according to federal government spokesman Steffen Hebestreit. CNN's Fred Pleitgen has more on Russia's response.

entries.title: With newfound powers, statehouse Democrats race to expand voting rights
entries.description: After strong electoral results in the midterm elections, Democrats in some key states are moving quickly this year on voting rights -- pushing ambitious plans to expand access to the ballot ahead of the 2024 presidential election.

entries.title: Passenger gives birth on Emirates flight from Tokyo to Dubai
entries.description: An Emirates flight from Tokyo Narita to Dubai International on January 19 touched down with an extra traveler on board, after a passenger gave birth in the air.

entries.title: 'Cringe': See Don Lemon's reaction to awkward moment at hearing
entries.description: Lawmakers quoted Taylor Swift lyrics during a congressional hearing where they also grilled Ticketmaster executives over the site crashing due to unprecedented demand for Swift's new concert tour.

entries.title: 'Leave him alone': Trump responds to Pence investigation
entries.description: A lawyer for former Vice President Mike Pence discovered about a dozen documents marked as classified at Pence's Indiana home last week, and he has turned those classified records over to the FBI, multiple sources familiar with the matter told CNN.

entries.title: From China to Japan, extreme cold is gripping East Asia. Experts say it's the 'new norm'
entries.description: Tens of millions of people across East Asia braved a severe cold snap Wednesday as subzero temperatures and heavy snow brought travel chaos during the Lunar New Year holiday, with climate experts warning that such extreme weather events had become the "new norm."

entries.title: Bratislava: Soviet city of the future still feels fresh and new
entries.description: There's a European capital whose crowning glory is a flying saucer that stands higher than the Statue of Liberty -- but this sci-fi city isn't troubling anyone's list of the continent's most visited destinations.

entries.title: 'Sesame Street' co-creator Lloyd Morrisett dies at 93
entries.description: "Sesame Street" co-creator Lloyd Morrisett has died at age 93, Sesame Workshop announced Monday.

entries.title: A Jewish family fleeing the Nazis sold a Picasso in 1938. Their heirs want it back
entries.description: One of Pablo Picasso's Blue Period paintings is at the center of a lawsuit between a Jewish family and New York's Guggenheim Museum.

entries.title: A tour guide and a tourist fell in love in Europe in 1971. They've been married for 50 years
entries.description: Carolyn Mazzie arrived at Amsterdam Schiphol Airport in September 1971, excited to embark on a three week tour of Europe.

entries.title: Ukrainian defense intelligence official: Putin's command structure is 'very problematic'
entries.description: CNN's Fred Pleitgen speaks to Vadym Skibitsky, Ukraine's Deputy Head of Defense Intelligence who says Russians are learning from their battlefield mistakes and making it harder for Ukraine's missiles to hit their ammunition depots and logistics hubs.

entries.title: Germany's parliament will debate sending Leopard tanks to Ukraine
A growing number of Russian officials are defecting to the West, offering up apparent secrets of the Putin regime's inner workings in exchange for safety
Peruvian families demand reparations for protester deaths amid reminders of a painful past
entries.description: "If something happens to me, don't cry," Leonardo Hancco told his wife, Ruth Barcena, the morning of December 15 in Peru's southern city of Ayacucho.

entries.title: Kanye West could be denied entry to Australia over anti-Semitic remarks, minister says
entries.description: Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, may not be suitable for an Australian visa because of his history of anti-Semitic remarks, a government minister said on Wednesday, as pressure mounted to deny entry to the award-winning US rapper.

entries.title: Confidence in London's police force crumbles as sex crime cases against officers pile up
entries.description: In a distinguished 30-year career with London's Metropolitan Police, Dal Babu has seen his fair share of shocking behavior.

entries.title: Jacinda Ardern bids emotional farewell as Chris Hipkins becomes New Zealand prime minister
entries.description: New Zealand welcomed a new prime minister on Wednesday, six days after Jacinda Ardern's shock resignation ahead of an upcoming election.

entries.title: Classified documents found at Pence's Indiana home
Cargo ship capsizes off Japan's coast with 22 aboard
entries.description: Five crew members have been rescued and efforts are underway to save 17 others after a cargo ship capsized off Japan's Nagasaki prefecture on Wednesday, the Japan Coast Guard told CNN.

entries.title: McCarthy officially denies Schiff and Swalwell seats on House Intelligence Committee
entries.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy on Tuesday officially denied Democratic Reps. Adam Schiff and Eric Swalwell seats on the House Intelligence Committee.

entries.title: Justin Bieber just sold his entire music catalog. Here's why companies are eager to strike these massive deals
entries.description: Music superstars are cashing in on a red-hot market.

entries.title: Extreme cold kills more than 150 people in Afghanistan, Taliban says
entries.description: At least 157 people have died in Afghanistan's harsh winter, a Taliban official said Tuesday, with the death toll doubling in less than a week as millions face bitter temperatures with minimal humanitarian aid.

entries.title: Japanese firm puts whale meat on sale in vending machines
entries.description: A Japanese whaling firm unveiled vending machines offering whale sashimi, whale steak and whale bacon in Yokohama on Tuesday in hopes of reviving sales of a food long in decline and shunned by many supermarkets.

entries.title: Ex-Trump official says rush to pack after Jan. 6 could be how Pence ended up with classified documents
entries.description: Former Trump White House official Alyssa Farah Griffin speaks with CNN's Anderson Cooper about the discovery of about a dozen documents marked classified in former Vice President Mike Pence's Indiana home last week.

entries.title: A New York mugging and bad checks: Podcaster reveals Santos' latest wild claims
entries.description: Newly surfaced video shows embattled Republican Congressman George Santos making more questionable claims during an interview with Rádio Novelo research director Flora Thomson-DeVeaux.

entries.title: Photo of a man posing with a Coca-Cola bottle in 1981 symbolized a cultural shift in China
entries.description: A young man stands grinning in Beijing's Forbidden City. It's the dead of winter, and one of his hands is buried deep into the pockets of his long overcoat to protect it from the chill. The other grasps the unmistakable contours of a glass Coca-Cola bottle.

entries.title: Full entertainment lineup for the 2023 Super Bowl has arrived
entries.description: The full entertainment lineup for the 2023 Super Bowl has arrived.
